text:
Near The Garage building,where the Bee's Knees Cafe and Botanico Restaurant 2nd level located are.

Walking on the metal-grilled walkway(there are plants) under it,is an interesting and relaxed walk to view many plants with attractive leaves. A heritage tree is planted here, Yellow Cheesewood.
Awesome place for a chill walk and explore with families and friends. There are some monitor lizards around but they are rather afraid of human but still watch out for it
There is always something interesting about every road you take, makes you curious about other paths.
A beautiful way to spend half a day wandering about all the varieties of plants and wood sculptures. There's a lot to do in this area.
breath of fresh air. Beautiful spot to relax and enjoy the view.
